thumb|220px|right|uncle remus in uncle remus , his songs and his sayings : the folk - lore of the old plantation , 1881 thumb|right|200px|"old plantation play song " , from uncle remus , his songs and his sayings : the folk - lore of the old plantation , 1881   uncle remus is the fictional title character and narrator of a collection of african - american folktales adapted and compiled by joel chandler harris , published in book form in 1881 .

literature : one of his last collections of tales , " uncle remus and the little boy " , was published posthumously in 1910

joel chandler harris